text: Orangeburg County is a county in the U.S. state of South Carolina. As of the 2020 census, 84,223 people lived there. Its county seat is Orangeburg. The county was formed in 1769. Orangeburg County comprises Orangeburg, SC Micropolitan Statistical Area, which is also included in the Columbia-Sumter- Orangeburg Combined Statistical Area. It is located in the Midlands region of South Carolina. == References == Category:18th-century establishments in South Carolina Category:1769 establishments in the Thirteen Colonies Category:South Carolina counties
